#: chaotic_pfc.comms.receiver:3 of
msgid ""
"Chaos-synchronisation demodulator. Implements the "
":class:`~chaotic_pfc.comms.protocols.Receiver` protocol — a callable that"
" extracts the original message from a transmitted (and possibly channel-"
"distorted) carrier."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.receiver:8 of
msgid ""
"Both receivers rely on the Pecora-Carroll synchronisation principle: "
"running a second copy of the Hénon oscillator driven by the received "
"signal causes it to track the transmitter's state after a short "
"transient. The recovered message is then extracted as the difference "
"between the driving signal and the local state estimate."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.receiver:14 of
msgid ""
"Two receivers are provided, mirroring "
":mod:`chaotic_pfc.comms.transmitter`:"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.receiver:17 of
msgid ":func:`receive` — 2-D Hénon demodulator. The message is recovered via"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.receiver:19 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\hat{m}[n] = \\frac{r[n] - y_1[n]}{\\mu}"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.receiver:23 of
msgid "where ``y_1`` is the local 2-D state driven by ``r``."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.receiver:25 of
msgid ""
":func:`receive_order_n` — higher-order demodulator. Uses the same FIR "
"filter the transmitter used. The carrier is taken from the filtered state"
" ``y[2][n]`` and the message follows the same formula with ``y_1`` "
"replaced by ``v = y[2]``."
msgstr ""

